member_recommendations_collection.recommendation:
"Ruchira is one of the best Manager with whom I have worked. I have started working with her when I was absolutely new into training and she was the one who helped during my initial days in learning & devleopment team of CROMA. She not only motivates her team to perform better but also empowers her subordinates.
She has got extremely sound and detail knowledge of HR and she is very supportive of her colleagues. If she believes that you have got the spark then she will always try and develop the individual.
She is very organized and protective manager, who will never let you face the burn directly, she works like a bridge between management and her team.
She has got very pleasing personalty and is equally focused and dedicated towards her goal.
It was a superb period working with her and wish to work again with her. With the kind of focus and commitment I am sure she will achieve all her goals.
Wish you great luck Mam."

Ruchira has an excellent eye for detail and is very particular about her work. Excellent Data Management skills blended with Creativity is one of her USP's. She not only motivates her subordinates to believe in themselves but also empowers them to achieve the impossible. In addition to a pleasing personality at office, she is equally hardworking and focused on achieving her goals. It's been an enlightening journey with her and am sure with the kind of commitment that she has for her work, sky is definitely not the limit.

Ruchira has been amongst the very forward looking, progressive leaders that I have worked with. She has been key to transformational HR work that took place in performance management in Axis Bank. Seamlessly she is able to move between strategic and tactical, while never losing her sight on the big picture. As a leader, she leads from the heart, and has a good sense of balance between people and goal orientation. Her agility is well proven through the successes she has achieved in all her first time roles, viz. in Banking, as a CHRO, etc. I wish her the very best for even more successes!

I have worked with mam during her tenure in Axis Bank and she has been a great mentor. Her ability to navigate complexities with composure is one of her greatest strength. She also has been able to bring in innovative ideas to the table and had created multiple best practice benchmarks in the industry. Wish you all the best mam and cherished working with you!!

A "thinking" CHRO, I found Ruchira to be open yet structured & with a "positive challenge" approach in people discussions.

She demonstrated an extremely scientific & effective approach to talent Acquisition & Management. 

Her acumen on "Leadership Development" is a benchmark, difficult to emulate. She has created leadership structures, developmental programs & a robust process for succession planning.
 
Her ability to proactively reach out, connect with (last mile) people, seek feedback take swift & impactful actions, define her stature as an outstanding CHRO
 
Her mentoring of a leader (internally) to fill the role she vacates, is testimony to her lasting legacy !

After knowing and working with Ruchira for 5+ years, can clearly say that we don't many in the business as good as Ruchira when it comes to HR Transformation - Ruchira is supremely good at her work, and an excellent leader!!
